channel.title: 562 Compiler Warning?
channel.description:
Hello,
In my 562 compiler I am getting two warnings.
Warning 1: [code]src\nq.java:106: warning: non-varargs call of varargs method with inexact argume nt type for last parameter; = (Long) method.invoke(runtime, null); ^ cast to Object for a varargs call cast to Object[] for a non-varargs call and to suppress this warning[/code]
Warning 2: [code]src\ti.java:52: warning: non-varargs call of varargs method with inexact argumen t type for last parameter; Integer integer = (Integer) method.invoke(runtime, null); ^ cast to Object for a varargs call cast to Object[] for a non-varargs call and to suppress this warning[/code]
I wouldn't bother with these warnings but when I run the client I get this error message:
[code]java.lang.NullPointerException at Class_x.a(Class_x.java:22) at Class_t.<init>(Class_t.java:12) at Class_x.a(Class_x.java:182) at Class_gd.a(Class_gd.java:150) at Class_sc.a(Class_sc.java:84) at client.j(client.java:2306) at client.d(client.java:683) at Class_a.c(Class_a.java:271) at Class_a.run(Class_a.java:693) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source)[/code]
So, I think there is some sort of a connection here but I don't know how to solve it. Would be great if someone could help. I have attached the two files to this post which contained the warning in.
Thanks!
